lfF7DPUEPQ0.title: Add a glossary to your document containing terms and acronyms - Glossaries package - LaTeX Course
description: How to add a glossary, terms, acronyms, and abbreviations to your LaTeX document.

A glossary is needed when you are using some field-specific concepts in your document.  A glossary is a list of terms in a particular domain of knowledge with definitions for those terms. For example, a glossary entry would explain to the reader the meaning of the word LaTeX by providing the following description: Is a markup language especially suited for scientific documents.

Generally, there are 2 types of entries in a glossary: terms and their definitions (as shown in the previous example), or acronyms (abbreviations) and their meaning. An acronym is a word formed from the initial letters in a phrase for example WHO is an acronym since it stands for World Health Organization (WHO).

The former method is a bit more complex but gives you more flexibility. The latter option is simpler to implement but can be only used if your website is a pure documentation website.

Algolia DocSearch works by crawling the content of your website every 24 hours and putting all the content in an Algolia index. The aim of this study was to determine how the sampling period affects the error in measuring skin temperature in longitudinal thermal comfort studies.
- iButton® can be used in longitudinal studies that aim to develop personalized thermal comfort models.

description: This video provides a brief overview about Cozie an iOS app for human comfort data collection. I will show you how Cozie works and you can become an Alpha tester. Please message us if you have additional questions or you are interested in contributing to this project.
